ism.In the 20th century, capitalist animal agriculture emerged with a twofold mission: to ruthlessly exploit animals for their labour time and enlarge human food supplies. The results of this process are clear. Animal-sourced foods have expanded exponentially. And simultaneously, hundreds of billions of animals confront humans and machines in brutal, antagonistic relations shaped by domination and resistance.  aMode of access: Internet via World Wide Web.  aIn English.0 aDescription based on online resource; title from PDF title page (publisher's Web site, viewed 06. Mrz 2024) 0aFood animalsxEconomic aspects. 0aFood animalsxMoral and ethical aspects. 0aFood supplyxMoral and ethical aspects. 0aLabor theory of value. 4aPhilosophy. 7aNATURE / Animal Rights.2bisacsh08iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe GruytertEdinburgh University Press Complete eBook-Package 2023z978311079764040uhttps://doi.org/10.1515/978139951808640uhttps://www.degruyter.com/isbn/9781399518086423Coveruhttps://www.degruyter.com/document/cover/isbn/9781399518086/original  a978-3-11-079764-0  Edinburgh University Press Complete eBook-Package 2023b2023  aEBA_EMB  aGBV-deGruyter-alles